<br>
My wis (with Paw in hand) is up to 186 .. but .. until level 37 or so it was less than yours .. and was only just enhanced (during level 41) from about 145 or so to its current level - and only by equipment I acquired solely on my own - no twinking .. no buying (except I had to pay to buy components for jewellry). <br>
<br>
You are fine the way you are. I know it might be a bit slower to level (though only if you lazily solo as I do - in a group I would imagine you can go with the flow of the group and do fine on that score as well).  <br>
<br>
The point is .. you don't need anywhere as much as you think you do .. as a druid anyway.  Don't be influenced by all you read here on the boards and see in game - by people who are into the 'equipment is king' mode.  The second point is .. have fun and don't worry. Things come in time .. and your time will come sooner than you think .. when you can begin questing for equipment.  <br>
<br>
I have no money to speak of even at this level, though I do have a bit of equipment that I can neither sell or wear (for instance, stormfeather talons which I got myself killing Stormfeather) - no one wants to buy them though they are super for the classes who could use them - at midlevels.  People are saturated with equipment these days .. so many choices .. so much affluence .. but don't worry about them .. think about your fun value.  You can do just about anything you want to do .. in time. <br>
<br>
Have fun.  Do things as cheaply as you can for now .. and don't let equipment stop you from trying things. I think you will find .. it doesn't really make that much difference. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubluefish2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bluefish2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#333399>(8/16/01 5:47:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3383.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: making money as a druid??</span><hr size=1> Well I've got 169 wisdom at lvl 54!! <br>
